org.omancode.rmt.cellreader
Class CellReaders

java.lang.Object
  org.omancode.rmt.cellreader.CellReaders

public final class CellReaders
extends Object

Utility class providing default cell readers.

Also provides methods for mapping from default cell reader name to the cell reader, and vice versa, as follows:

String name Default cell reader
"boolean" BOOLEAN
"character" CHARACTER
"double" DOUBLE
"integer" INTEGER
"string" STRING
"optional integer" OPTIONAL_INTEGER
"optional double" OPTIONAL_DOUBLE

Version:
$Revision: 29 $
Author:
Oliver Mannion

compose

public static <F,G> CellReader<F> compose(CellReader<F> f,
                                          CellReader<G> g)
Composes one CellReader with another to return a new CellReader according to function composition.

Type Parameters:
F - type returned by cell reader f
G - type returned by cell reader g
Parameters:
f - the cell reader f.
g - the cell reader g to compose with f.
Returns:
a new CellReader h such that h(x) = f(g(x)), where x represents a parameter accepted by g.
